                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">704.4181/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-28T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 28, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Your telegram 55, August 8, 5 p.m. By mistake the Belgian Consul General
                    filed the protest yesterday associating me with it. This morning I informed the
                    Diplomatic Cabinet that the association was premature and to be disregarded. Mr.
                        Barbanson<note n="66" xml:id="d756fn66">Albert Barbanson, Belgian Consul
                        General and Dean of the Consular Corps at Casablanca.</note> did the
                    same.</p>
                <p>The Swiss and the Japanese representatives joined in making the protest but the
                    Greek received instructions not to do so under the present circumstances and the
                    Spaniard held that the time had passed.</p>
                <p>Under the circumstances and to save time may I telegraph the protest in the
                    clear.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
